<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68b292a-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10308"><num value="10308">§ 10308.</num><heading> Foreign engagements</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When a seaman is engaged outside the United States, the agreement required by <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s10302">section 10302 of this title</ref> shall be signed in the presence of a consular officer. If a consular officer is not available at the port of engagement, the seaman may be engaged, and the agreement shall be signed in the next port at which a consular officer is available.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68b292b-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/564">97 Stat. 564</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/206/tIV/s406">Pub. L. 103–206, title IV, § 406</ref>, <date date="1993-12-20">Dec. 20, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2436">107 Stat. 2436</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf68b292c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
